ses and families and grew the bank's assets from $4 million to over $400 million. in 1997, he entered politics as chairman of the boulder country (PARTY NAME)s and in 1999, was elected chairman of the colorado (PARTY NAME) party. in 2002, he was elected to the u.s. house of representatives from the 7th congressional district. in 2006, congressman beauprez was the (PARTY NAME) nominee for governor of colorado. today, he lives in indian peaks and operates a new web site and e-magazine called <em>a line of sight</em>, which advocates common-sense solutions to our country's policy issues. he also serves as president of the newly formed rocky mountain community foundation.</p></span>



